rts his social advancement and the self-fashioning of his gentle image, while placing him in the context of current discussions of gentry culture. What makes Newton even more noteworthy is that he was among the unsung and little known stratum of English society historians have labelled the 'lesser' gentry. As such, this book provides the first comprehensive biography of an early Tudor gentleman. Dr DEBORAH YOUNGS is lecturer in medieval history at Swansea University.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aGentryzGreat BritainvBiography. 4aEarly Modern History. 4aMedieval History. 4aModern History. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Personal Memoirs.2bisacsh  aEnglish society.  aHumphrey Newton.  acourtly love lyrics.  aearly Tudor gentleman.  afamily life.  agentry culture.  agentry life.  ahistorical specificity.  alanded estate.  alegal work.  apiety.  aprivate lives.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013z978311143139040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978184615645840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781846156458423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781846156458/original  a978-3-11-143139-0  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013b2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles